data.text:
For 16 years, Cardinal Aloysius Ambrozic was in charge of the largest Catholic archdiocese in Canada. Home to some 1.7 million Roman Catholics spread across an area spanning 13,000 square kilometres, the diocese of Toronto hosted World Youth Day, the large global rally gathering Catholic youth to meet with the Pope in 2002.

Seven hundred and fity thousand young people from all over the world turned up in Toronto over a five-day period in 2002, to meet with Benedict XVI. World Youth Day Toronto was the largest gathering of Catholic youth in Canadian history and as Cardinal of Toronto (he had been appointed to the role in 1998) Ambrozic had a key role in the eventâ€™s organisation.
